Both methods are called when processing **write** operations (add, write-attribute). 

**4. `registerReadOnlyAttribute` never invokes correctors:**

In `controller/src/main/java/org/jboss/as/controller/registry/ConcreteResourceRegistration.java:427-434`:
```java
@Override
public void registerReadOnlyAttribute(final AttributeDefinition definition, final OperationStepHandler readHandler) {
    // ...
    AttributeAccess aa = new AttributeAccess(AccessType.READ_ONLY, storage, readHandler, null, definition);
    storeAttribute(definition, aa);
